          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Europe to up its defense</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/french-president-emmanuel-macron.png" alt="French President Emmanuel Macron" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;">French President Emmanuel Macron. Credits: Bob Edme/AFP via Getty Images</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
         
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">French President Emmanuel Macron is pushing for a significant increase in <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-04-03-2025-h2-2-european-defense-spending?source=website" target="_blank">European defense spending</a>. Macron calls for nations to allocate 3 to 3.5 percent of their GDP to military budgets. His remarks come after an emergency summit on Ukraine in London. France spends 2.1 percent of its GDP on defense, just above NATO’s 2 percent benchmark, which it only recently met. </p>

          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Macron argues that with Russia dedicating 10 percent of its GDP to military expenditures, Europe must urgently strengthen its defenses. He suggests using unused EU funds, common borrowing, or the European Stability Mechanism to fund this boost, estimating an initial need of $209 Bn. He also hinted at revising France’s military budget despite lacking a parliamentary majority.</p>

          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">This push aligns with the growing pressure within NATO to raise the defense spending target. At a summit in June, leaders are expected to set a higher goal, potentially beyond 3 percent. Europe scrambles to compose a response to Washington's new Ukraine policy, in which it appears to be pivoting away from Europe and seeking conciliation with Russia.</p>
        </mj-text>
