            <strong>🇯🇵 Japan skips UN nuclear arms conference to avoid 'wrong message'</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Japan has <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-04-03-2025-br2-5-has-opted-out-of-attending-a-un-conference?source=website" target="_blank">opted out of attending a UN conference</a> on the nuclear weapons ban treaty. It cited the importance of US nuclear deterrence for national security. Chief Cabinet Secretary Yoshimasa Hayashi stated that participation would send the "wrong message" and interfere with Japan’s security strategy. Japan is the only country to have suffered nuclear attacks.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Despite this, it has refused to sign the treaty, arguing it is ineffective without nuclear states' participation. Survivors and activists have criticized the government’s stance and urged Japan to at least observe the conference. PM Shigeru Ishiba is a proponent of nuclear deterrence. He has emphasized the need for extended US nuclear protection, particularly amid rising tensions with China.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
